</head>

<body class="body2">
    <div class="container">
        <br>
        <!-- Image card -->
        <div class="card bg-primary mb-3" >
        <div class="text-center my-4">
            <h1 id="heading">OMW! Instructions</h1>
            <br>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="card bg-white mb-3" >
        <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
            
            <img src="/images/instructions.png" class="img-fluid rounded-start" alt="WordleImage" width="600px" height="550px">
        </div>
        <div class="col">
        <div class="my-4">
            <!-- Singleplayer instructions -->
            <h2 id="heading2">SinglePlayer</h2>
            <br>
            <h4 id="paragraph"> The goal of the game is to guess the hidden five letter word.
                <br>
                The game is played on a five wide and six long grid. Your five letter words are placed in the grid.
                All guesses must be real words.
                You have 6 guesses to get the correct word but you will be rewarded for guesses along the way.
                <br>
                If a letter in your guess turns
                <span class="Yellowtext">Yellow</span>
                then the letter in your guess are correct but in the wrong position.So the letter is in one of the other positions.
                <br>
                If a letter in your guess turns
                <span class="Greentext">Green</span>
                then the letter in your guess is the correct letter and in the right location. 
                <br>
                Using this information you can try and find the correct word without running out of guesses.
                There is a helpful keyboard below that shows you your guesses, both 
                <span class="GreyText">wrong</span>
                ,
                <span class="Yellowtext">yellow</span> 
                and 
                <span class="Greentext">green</span>
                .
            </h4>
            <br>
        </div>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    </div>
        
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card bg-white mb-3" >
            <div class="row">
            <div class="col">
                
                <img src="/images/instructions.png" class="img-fluid rounded-start" alt="WordleImage" width="600px" height="550px">
            </div>
            <div class="col">
        <div class="my-4">
            <h2 id="heading2">MultiPlayer</h2>
            <br>
             <!-- Multiplayer instructions -->
            <h4 id="paragraph">
                During versus MultiPlayer you cannot see the letters that your opponent has guessed but you can see the
                <span class="Yellowtext">Yellow</span>
                and
                <span class="Greentext">Green</span>
                boxes that they have guessed so far.
                <br>
                The first player to guess the correct five letter word is the winner.
                <br>
                <br>
                During word challenge Multiplayer player one sets a five letter word for player two  to guess.
                <br>
                If the word is not guessed player one wins. If the word is guessed player two wins.


            </h4>
            </div>
    <button style = "position:absolute; right:80px; bottom:20px;" class="button" id="Back" name="backButton">Back</button>        
             <!-- Back Button position bottom right -->
</body>

